t for several Gyr, we argue that late-time\nperturbations of planetary systems most likely explain these trends, although\nadditional perturbations at birth may contribute too. This suggests that\nplanetary system properties are not just affected by stellar clustering in\ntheir immediate surroundings, but by galaxy-scale processes throughout their\nevolution. We conclude by discussing the main open questions towards\nunderstanding the diversity of physical processes that together set planetary\nsystem architectures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Sep 2021 18:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-15"}
